{
  "local_port": 55934,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you remove your Gmail Profile picture?",
  "response": "To remove your Gmail profile picture, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Gmail**: Go to your Gmail account by visiting the Gmail website and logging in if you haven't already.\n\n2. **Access Google Account Settings**:\n   - Click on your profile picture or initial at the top right corner of the Gmail page.\n   - From the dropdown menu, click on \"Manage your Google Account.\"\n\n3. **Navigate to Personal Info**:\n   - Once in your Google Account page, click on \"Personal info\" from the navigation menu on the left side.\n\n4. **Edit Profile Picture**:\n   - Scroll down to the \"Profile\" section. You will see your current profile picture here.\n   - Click on the camera icon that appears when you hover over your profile picture.\n\n5. **Remove the Picture**:\n   - A window will pop up giving you options to take a new photo or upload one from your computer.\n   - At the bottom of this window, you will see a \"Remove\" button. Click on it.\n\n6. **Confirm Removal**:\n   - A confirmation dialog will appear asking if you're sure you want to remove your profile picture. Click \"Remove\" to confirm.\n\n7. **Picture Removed**:\n   - Your profile picture will be removed, and you will see the default silhouette icon or your initial instead.\n\nThese steps should successfully remove your Gmail profile picture. Remember that this change will be reflected across all Google services where your profile picture is displayed.",
